1
00:01:46,520 --> 00:01:50,880
=Dear Enemy=

2
00:01:57,480 --> 00:01:58,640
Do you know

3
00:01:59,230 --> 00:02:00,790
how Chen Mian left today?

4
00:02:05,150 --> 00:02:07,030
Honey, can you get me a shirt?

5
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:40,640
Thanks.

6
00:02:58,790 --> 00:02:59,270
This...

7
00:03:00,670 --> 00:03:02,320
This doesn't look right.

8
00:03:02,710 --> 00:03:03,640
Don't you think

9
00:03:03,950 --> 00:03:04,950
it shrunk?

10
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:08,390
Sorry, wrong piece.

11
00:03:27,160 --> 00:03:28,040
What do you mean?

12
00:03:29,555 --> 00:03:31,333
What is this supposed to mean?

13
00:03:32,990 --> 00:03:34,510
Are you seeing someone?

14
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:42,600
I thought

15
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:43,880
you didn't care.

16
00:03:49,080 --> 00:03:49,880
Who?

17
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:53,040
Who is that man?

18
00:03:54,990 --> 00:03:56,990
Are you divorcing me because of him?

19
00:03:57,670 --> 00:03:59,160
If you're curious,

20
00:03:59,760 --> 00:04:01,110
hire someone to follow me too.

21
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:41,710
From now on,

22
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:44,200
stop calling me "Honey".

23
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:53,510
Do you think

24
00:04:53,510 --> 00:04:55,240
I've read too many romance novels,

25
00:04:55,733 --> 00:04:56,830
and it made me feel like

26
00:04:56,830 --> 00:04:58,710
I had to stab him back

27
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,560
just to get even?

28
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:06,880
Am I being childish?

29
00:05:14,710 --> 00:05:16,800
I always said you were dramatic.

30
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:19,800
But I think I'm worse.

31
00:05:20,350 --> 00:05:21,350
It's hilarious.

32
00:05:32,910 --> 00:05:33,880
To be honest,

33
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:37,880
for my marriage

34
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:39,640
to end up like this,

35
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:44,120
I know I'm also to blame.

36
00:05:47,350 --> 00:05:48,800
Sometimes, I wonder,

37
00:05:50,470 --> 00:05:51,440
and

38
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:53,320
I reflect on myself.

39
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:57,710
Was I too dependent,

40
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:00,710
investing all my time and energy

41
00:06:00,710 --> 00:06:02,080
into the marriage,

42
00:06:03,470 --> 00:06:04,950
only to end up where I am today?

43
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:07,240
You...

44
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,680
Are you all right?

45
00:06:14,030 --> 00:06:15,760
Why should you reflect on yourself?

46
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:19,830
Do you think

47
00:06:19,830 --> 00:06:21,880
Chen Mian's reflecting on anything
right now?

48
00:06:24,710 --> 00:06:26,830
You've done so much better.

49
00:06:31,590 --> 00:06:32,390
You know,

50
00:06:33,390 --> 00:06:35,680
you're overthinking it.

51
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,440
But you're right about one thing.

52
00:06:42,270 --> 00:06:43,640
You should put all your energy

53
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:45,350
into yourself.

54
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:50,120
No one is more important than you.

55
00:07:06,553 --> 00:07:10,710
=Episode 24=
(We Are Dear Enemies)

56
00:07:12,270 --> 00:07:14,440
You ingrate!

57
00:07:14,590 --> 00:07:16,200
I must've been blind

58
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:18,560
to think you were the honest one!

59
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:20,200
You gang up with outsiders against me!

60
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:22,320
I'm your brother, you know?

61
00:07:40,270 --> 00:07:41,910
But you are wrong.

62
00:08:23,255 --> 00:08:27,150
(Yancheng West Station)

63
00:08:40,230 --> 00:08:40,870
Hello?

64
00:08:42,750 --> 00:08:44,280
I heard everything.

65
00:08:48,110 --> 00:08:49,800
You left in a rush.

66
00:08:50,950 --> 00:08:53,470
I applied for the transfer
to the branch hospital.

67
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:55,470
That's good.

68
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,470
You can train yourself there.

69
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:01,990
Are you leaving now?

70
00:09:10,590 --> 00:09:11,520
Well...

71
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:14,710
All the best to you.

72
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:17,920
Take care of yourself.

73
00:10:10,950 --> 00:10:13,640
(Six Months Later)

74
00:10:36,209 --> 00:10:39,040
(The End)

75
00:11:04,680 --> 00:11:05,800
You're exhausted.

76
00:11:05,990 --> 00:11:07,280
You've been working so hard.

77
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:09,630
Treat yourself to a nice meal.

78
00:11:10,230 --> 00:11:12,200
You deserve it.

79
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:28,160
Welcome.

80
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:30,400
Here.

81
00:11:31,230 --> 00:11:31,680
Thank you.

82
00:11:31,680 --> 00:11:32,350
You're welcome.

83
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:01,040
Is this seat taken?

84
00:12:11,555 --> 00:12:12,350
What a small world.

85
00:12:12,990 --> 00:12:13,680
Yeah.

86
00:12:16,280 --> 00:12:17,040
I heard

87
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:20,350
you're really into golf lately.

88
00:12:22,230 --> 00:12:23,400
I'm getting older.

89
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:25,320
I have to watch my back.

90
00:12:27,110 --> 00:12:28,080
True.

91
00:12:29,110 --> 00:12:30,870
You know a lot about me.

92
00:12:31,870 --> 00:12:32,630
Of course.

93
00:12:32,950 --> 00:12:34,110
You're a big shot.

94
00:12:34,110 --> 00:12:35,750
It's hard not to know.

95
00:12:36,920 --> 00:12:37,630
Why?

96
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:39,950
Are you

97
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:41,750
bowing down
to the evil food industry now?

98
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:43,470
Absolutely not.

99
00:12:45,933 --> 00:12:48,130
(New Dishes Available)
They used to serve only set meats.

100
00:12:48,133 --> 00:12:49,520
Now you can order a la carte.

101
00:12:49,630 --> 00:12:50,750
To be precise,

102
00:12:50,870 --> 00:12:53,320
the evil power turns over a new leaf

103
00:12:53,710 --> 00:12:54,920
and bows down to us.

104
00:12:58,830 --> 00:12:59,870
They surrender to you.

105
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:06,830
Do you want some more?

106
00:13:15,122 --> 00:13:16,002
Ms. Luo,

107
00:13:16,110 --> 00:13:17,600
you're producing good scripts now,

108
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:19,400
and your acting

109
00:13:19,590 --> 00:13:21,110
is improving as well.

110
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:22,800
All thanks to you.

111
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:24,230
I learned from the best.

112
00:13:26,830 --> 00:13:27,990
What's that saying?

113
00:13:28,990 --> 00:13:30,040
"If the student succeeds,

114
00:13:30,111 --> 00:13:31,230
the master has to starve."

115
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:34,400
That sounds familiar.

116
00:13:42,230 --> 00:13:43,590
Actually,

117
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:45,990
I can guess

118
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:47,830
how you reacted at that time.

119
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:51,080
You didn't lose your temper.

120
00:13:52,280 --> 00:13:53,280
Am I right?

121
00:13:54,058 --> 00:13:55,600
(Chen Mian)

122
00:14:03,990 --> 00:14:04,710
Hello?

123
00:14:04,777 --> 00:14:05,560
The money is gone.

124
00:14:06,110 --> 00:14:07,080
All gone!

125
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:10,950
Why weren't you keeping an eye on it?

126
00:14:28,292 --> 00:14:31,560
(Luo Man)

127
00:14:47,280 --> 00:14:49,160
I had a feeling at that time.

128
00:14:50,280 --> 00:14:51,400
But...

129
00:14:52,080 --> 00:14:54,680
I feel like something about you

130
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:56,950
is off.

131
00:14:57,870 --> 00:14:58,990
Maybe

132
00:14:59,870 --> 00:15:00,950
you're being too nice.

133
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:04,080
And it makes me uncomfortable.

134
00:15:08,870 --> 00:15:09,950
But?

135
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:35,920
Mr. Zhou,

136
00:15:35,990 --> 00:15:37,733
you always leave your sentences hanging.

137
00:15:48,750 --> 00:15:49,590
I'm not lying.

138
00:15:51,750 --> 00:15:53,230
I'm telling the truth.

139
00:15:58,080 --> 00:15:58,800
I know.

140
00:16:03,590 --> 00:16:05,630
And that's what

141
00:16:06,350 --> 00:16:07,280
made it

142
00:16:08,520 --> 00:16:09,560
even scarier.

143
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:18,470
I'm a little tipsy now,

144
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:22,950
so I'll tell you the truth.

145
00:16:25,630 --> 00:16:27,630
I know you really liked me.

146
00:16:29,470 --> 00:16:30,590
Maybe even

147
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:32,280
loved me.

148
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:34,520
Not much,

149
00:16:34,520 --> 00:16:36,200
but just a little, give or take,

150
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:36,990
right?

151
00:16:38,990 --> 00:16:40,950
That tiny bit of love

152
00:16:40,950 --> 00:16:42,710
is already

153
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:45,200
rare in you.

154
00:16:46,470 --> 00:16:47,920
But so what?

155
00:16:48,990 --> 00:16:49,680
Even though

156
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:52,560
it's rare to have
that tiny bit of love from you,

157
00:16:52,560 --> 00:16:54,350
you still used it

158
00:16:54,630 --> 00:16:55,800
and calculated with it.

159
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:58,280
In the end,

160
00:16:58,440 --> 00:16:59,950
you trapped yourself.

161
00:17:07,150 --> 00:17:08,190
This whole thing

162
00:17:08,190 --> 00:17:09,520
may look like

163
00:17:09,520 --> 00:17:11,240
it's about Chen Mian and Chen Kaixi,

164
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:16,110
but it's actually about us too, right?

165
00:17:16,630 --> 00:17:18,240
But I didn't hurt you.

166
00:17:20,430 --> 00:17:21,350
Instead,

167
00:17:22,080 --> 00:17:24,630
you helped Chen Kaixin beat Chen Mian.

168
00:17:25,560 --> 00:17:27,110
What did you get out of that?

169
00:17:35,590 --> 00:17:38,320
Why does everything have to come
with benefits?

170
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:44,560
This question sounds unfamiliar to you.

171
00:17:47,110 --> 00:17:48,390
You once said

172
00:17:48,590 --> 00:17:51,110
we were the same in nature.

173
00:17:54,040 --> 00:17:54,830
Selfish,

174
00:17:55,080 --> 00:17:56,110
ambitious,

175
00:17:56,390 --> 00:17:58,480
and desperate to climb to reach the top.

176
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:00,280
Back then,

177
00:18:00,320 --> 00:18:00,960
I agreed.

178
00:18:01,955 --> 00:18:03,390
That was exactly who I was.

179
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:06,350
But then I realized it wasn't.

180
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:08,240
We're not the same.

181
00:18:08,830 --> 00:18:11,390
You're much harder on yourself
than I am.

182
00:18:13,190 --> 00:18:14,630
To put it bluntly,

183
00:18:15,670 --> 00:18:17,320
you're more selfish.

184
00:18:19,190 --> 00:18:21,590
Because when I make decisions,

185
00:18:22,311 --> 00:18:23,755
I don't want anything in return.

186
00:18:24,830 --> 00:18:27,480
I do it because it makes me feel great.

187
00:18:27,760 --> 00:18:28,830
Is that okay?

188
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:38,000
You and Chen Mian
are cut from the same cloth.

189
00:18:40,910 --> 00:18:42,110
You're selfish,

190
00:18:42,350 --> 00:18:43,480
cold,

191
00:18:43,590 --> 00:18:44,910
and ruthless.

192
00:18:45,910 --> 00:18:47,150
How does that saying go?

193
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:48,830
"You're cruel

194
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:50,320
because you understand."

195
00:18:59,670 --> 00:19:00,110
Here.

196
00:19:11,760 --> 00:19:13,960
Sometimes, I do feel bad for you.

197
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:17,000
I think

198
00:19:17,080 --> 00:19:18,350
you're kind of pitiful.

199
00:19:21,870 --> 00:19:23,590
The way you climbed

200
00:19:23,590 --> 00:19:25,320
cost you your pride.

201
00:19:25,960 --> 00:19:27,040
I wonder,

202
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:29,110
how can I expect someone

203
00:19:29,110 --> 00:19:31,320
who's never truly

204
00:19:31,320 --> 00:19:32,670
been loved

205
00:19:32,670 --> 00:19:33,320
to learn how

206
00:19:33,350 --> 00:19:35,240
to love someone else?

207
00:19:36,430 --> 00:19:38,830
That's a tall order.

208
00:19:39,390 --> 00:19:40,280
So

209
00:19:40,670 --> 00:19:42,720
your selfishness is understandable.

210
00:19:43,480 --> 00:19:44,870
I guess

211
00:19:45,390 --> 00:19:46,910
you're lonely.

212
00:19:52,150 --> 00:19:53,000
Well,

213
00:19:54,150 --> 00:19:54,800
you

214
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,080
are like a maze.

215
00:19:57,390 --> 00:19:58,560
Open one door,

216
00:19:58,720 --> 00:19:59,720
and there's another.

217
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:00,960
And open that,

218
00:20:00,960 --> 00:20:02,110
there's another behind.

219
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:05,320
So many doors.

220
00:20:05,670 --> 00:20:06,870
They're hard to open.

221
00:20:08,320 --> 00:20:09,870
It makes people believe

222
00:20:09,870 --> 00:20:11,430
that when they open the last one,

223
00:20:11,430 --> 00:20:12,240
there'll be treasure

224
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:14,240
in the room.

225
00:20:14,630 --> 00:20:16,630
But when I finally got there

226
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:19,040
and walked into the room,

227
00:20:21,670 --> 00:20:22,760
I realized it was empty.

228
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:30,110
Aren't all men like that?

229
00:20:33,910 --> 00:20:35,000
Me.

230
00:20:35,960 --> 00:20:37,080
Chen Mian.

231
00:20:41,350 --> 00:20:42,390
What about Fang Chi?

232
00:20:44,390 --> 00:20:45,960
Isn't he the same?

233
00:20:49,240 --> 00:20:50,560
Or

234
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:56,000
is he just not capable
of being like us yet?

235
00:21:05,910 --> 00:21:06,480
Zhou Musun,

236
00:21:06,480 --> 00:21:08,430
you look pathetic right now.

237
00:21:10,948 --> 00:21:13,968
(Black Ship)

238
00:21:29,156 --> 00:21:32,490
(Black Ship)

239
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:37,280
("Our Times" Work Group,
Producer: Tomorrow at 6 AM.)

240
00:21:37,280 --> 00:21:38,480
(Golden Palace Banquet Hall.)

241
00:21:38,480 --> 00:21:40,350
(It's the press conference
of our documentary)

242
00:21:40,350 --> 00:21:41,720
(Noted.)
(Please gather at the venue)

243
00:21:41,720 --> 00:21:43,266
(before 5: 30 PM tomorrow.)

244
00:21:43,288 --> 00:21:45,640
(There'll be a celebration banquet
in the evening.)

245
00:21:45,644 --> 00:21:46,800
(Everyone must come.)

246
00:21:48,695 --> 00:21:51,390
(Luo Man: Okay.)

247
00:21:55,190 --> 00:21:57,520
Thank you all so much during this time.

248
00:22:00,777 --> 00:22:02,520
When we were shooting
at the hospital...

249
00:22:02,560 --> 00:22:03,390
Director.

250
00:22:04,150 --> 00:22:04,590
Luo Man.

251
00:22:04,590 --> 00:22:05,430
Congrats.

252
00:22:05,430 --> 00:22:07,390
I'm reporting
to the department head now.

253
00:22:07,888 --> 00:22:08,390
Hello, Sir.

254
00:22:08,390 --> 00:22:09,560
Hello.

255
00:22:10,190 --> 00:22:11,520
- Ms. Luo Man.
- Ms. Man.

256
00:22:14,720 --> 00:22:15,430
Ms. Luo Man.

257
00:22:16,390 --> 00:22:17,110
Sun.

258
00:23:11,430 --> 00:23:12,590
Can you tie it for me?

259
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:40,960
You haven't learned it yet?

260
00:24:29,644 --> 00:24:31,240
Guys, we're about to enter the venue.

261
00:24:35,590 --> 00:24:36,350
Go ahead.

262
00:24:45,590 --> 00:24:47,280
During these months,

263
00:24:47,630 --> 00:24:50,040
all of us went through hardships
and joys together.

264
00:24:50,150 --> 00:24:50,910
There were

265
00:24:50,910 --> 00:24:53,390
many unforgettable moments.

266
00:24:53,800 --> 00:24:54,760
I want to tell everyone

267
00:24:54,760 --> 00:24:56,520
(Celebration Banquet)
that you've done

268
00:24:56,666 --> 00:24:58,333
(Medical Humanistic Documentary)
a great job.

269
00:25:00,760 --> 00:25:02,190
The core of the documentary

270
00:25:02,430 --> 00:25:04,040
is truth.

271
00:25:04,280 --> 00:25:06,320
We capture reality,

272
00:25:06,350 --> 00:25:09,000
express sincerity,
and show genuine emotions.

273
00:25:09,350 --> 00:25:10,560
That's what

274
00:25:10,560 --> 00:25:12,390
I've always asked of myself

275
00:25:12,390 --> 00:25:14,910
and the team.

276
00:25:15,390 --> 00:25:16,320
Today,

277
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:17,800
I'd like to take this opportunity

278
00:25:18,040 --> 00:25:19,430
to express

279
00:25:19,430 --> 00:25:21,280
our highest respect

280
00:25:21,280 --> 00:25:24,000
to all medical workers here.

281
00:25:24,080 --> 00:25:25,000
Thank you.

282
00:25:26,800 --> 00:25:27,760
Cheers.

283
00:25:28,280 --> 00:25:29,190
Good job.

284
00:25:39,830 --> 00:25:40,910
What scene is this?

285
00:25:41,480 --> 00:25:42,430
So sweet.

286
00:25:43,110 --> 00:25:44,720
What a couple.

287
00:25:45,488 --> 00:25:47,150
- Dr. Liu?
- That guy is Fang Chi, right?

288
00:25:47,150 --> 00:25:48,150
Is that Dr. Liu?

289
00:25:48,800 --> 00:25:50,240
Who's the woman?

290
00:25:51,560 --> 00:25:54,280
Who's she?

291
00:25:54,280 --> 00:25:55,480
Don't look at me.

292
00:25:56,080 --> 00:25:57,040
It's not me.

293
00:25:58,590 --> 00:25:59,430
Eat the dishes.

294
00:26:00,430 --> 00:26:02,520
Fang Chi surely knows who she is.

295
00:26:02,520 --> 00:26:04,040
Who's she, Fang Chi?

296
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:07,870
So mysterious.

297
00:26:08,080 --> 00:26:08,720
Come on,

298
00:26:08,960 --> 00:26:10,240
everyone.

299
00:26:10,390 --> 00:26:13,040
